  "texts": [
    "User feedback U i is processed through function F, generating a binary outcome indicating the presence of an error.",
    "The function E(U i) quantifies the feedback's impact, contributing to the model's learning adjustments.Feedback Score S = n i=1 E(U i) • W (i),where W (i) represents a weighting factor for feedback instance i, calculated based on the recency and frequency of similar feedback.",
    "The model's adjustment mechanism is governed by:∆M = λ • ∇ M S, M new = M old + η • ∆M,where λ is the learning rate, ∇ M S represents the gradient of the feedback score with respect to the model parameters M, and η is a scaling factor to modulate the update magnitude.",
    "This complex interplay of user feedback and model adaptation ensures that the system not only corrects identified errors but also evolves in response to emerging patterns and changes in language use.",
    "By incorporating these mathematical formulations, the feedback loop mechanism optimally adjusts the error detection and correction modules, leading to a continual reduction in error frequency and an enhancement in overall system reliability and user satisfaction."
